\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 Configuring DoubleCommand
\f0\b0\fs24 \

\fs8 \
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\ql\qnatural

\fs24 \cf0 To configure DoubleCommand requires some basic maths ability and a text editor (like this one). You only need to edit the file /Library/StartupItems/DoubleCommand/DoubleCommand, changing the number at the end of the line:\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural

\f2 \cf0 /usr/sbin/sysctl -w dc.config=1\

\f0 to a number calculated below and save the file. Then either copy that line into a Terminal and press return, or just restart your computer. Unfortunately this version and Mac OS X 10.2 do not play well together and you will need to run this command in the Terminal after every restart.\
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\ql\qnatural
\cf0 \
The table below shows a list of numbers and what functionality they activate. To activate more than one at a time, simply add the numbers together. For example, I like enter -> command and shift+delete -> forward delete, so I use 1 + 16384 = 16385. So my file has a line that looks like:\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural

\f2 \cf0 /usr/sbin/sysctl -w dc.config=16385\
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\ql\qnatural

\f0 \cf0 \
Where command, option, etc are used it means any command, option, etc keys on your keyboard. It is not possible at this stage to only change for example the right option key to something else, you must change both option keys. This issue is under investigation.\
\
0 - do nothing\
1 - enter -> command\
2 - enter -> control\
4 - enter -> option\
8 - enter -> fn (partial support, cursor keys only)\
16 - command -> option\
32 - command -> control\
64 - option -> command\
128 - option -> fn (not yet available)\
256 - control -> command\
512 - control <-> option (swap)\
1024 - control -> fn (not yet available)\
2048 - caps lock -> control (partial, sticky)\
4096 - fn -> control\
8192 - numpad . switch\
16384 - shift delete -> forward delete\
32768 - disable option and command\
65536 - PC style Home and End keys\
\
\
